Florida author Diana Abu-Jaber will discuss her new novel, Fencing With the King, in conversation with former journalist and BayCare communications director Joni James at 7 p.m. May 24 at Tombolo Books, 2153 First Ave. S, St. Petersburg. Free; RSVP at tombolobooks.com/events. Clearwater author Jan M. Walton will discuss her novel River Avenue at 5 p.m. May 25  at the Clearwater Beach Library, 69 Bay Esplanade, Clearwater. Free. For information, call (727) 562-4970. Poet Victoria Dym will launch and sign her new book, Spontaneous, joined by poets Charmaine Jennings and Wally B. Jennings, at 7:30 p.m. May 28 at Powerstories Theater, 2105 W Kennedy Blvd., Tampa. Free; wine and cheese and an open mic follow the reading. Book Talk is a listing of in-person author appearances in the Tampa Bay area in the coming week. To place an item in Book Talk, send author’s name, book title, appearance time, date, venue name and address, admission cost (if any) and a contact phone number to cbancroft@tampabay.com, with “Book Talk” in the subject line. Deadline is 14 days before publication.